This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with filtering and summarizing relevant information from a large stream of data. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are commonly used in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of trending topics and hashtags, which are related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The framework proposed in the paper involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with data stream processing, which is related to the Software Engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
